'''''Shiloh: Grant's Trial in the West''''' is a 1987 video game published by [[Strategic Simulations]].

==Gameplay==
''Shiloh: Grant's Trial in the West'' is a game in which the [[Battle of Shiloh]] is covered using turns that last for an hour-and-a-half.<ref name="CGW43"/>

==Reception==
Jay C. Selover reviewed the game for ''[[Computer Gaming World]]'', and stated that "''Shiloh'' locks up SSI's position as the producer of the finest operational level American Civil War system to date."<ref name="CGW43">{{cite magazine |last=Selover |first=Jay C. |title=Bullets for Breakfast: The Battle of Shiloh |magazine=Computer Gaming World |date=January 1988 |volume=1 |issue=43 |pages=12â€“14, 16}}</ref>

